title: A Popular History of Ireland: from the Earliest Period to the Emancipation of the Catholics, Book 03
creator: D'Arcy McGee
description: Thomas D'Arcy McGee was an Irish refugee and a father of the Canadian confederation. His work on Irish history is comprehensive, encompassing twelve books; book 3 begins with the fortune of the family of Brian Boru and continues through the rise of the O'Conors to the political, economic, and religious condition of the island prior to the English invasion. (Summary by Sibella Denton) M4B audiobook of Complete Series
